    "description": "This allows the user to tell annotate_halos which fields to get information like\r\nthe halo centers and halo radii, and allows greater flexibility.\r\n\r\nFor example, here are halos annotated using 'virial_radius' as found by the halo finder for circle size, and 'particle_position_*' fields as found by the halo finder for circle position. This is what is normally done.\r\n\r\n![projection_halo_normal.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/jzpo5A/images/594144477-projection_halo_normal.png)\r\n\r\nI've populated the 'radius_200' field using the virial quantities recipe and found new halo positions using the iterative center of mass call back and populated the 'halo_position_*' fields with the new halo positions. I can now annotate the same projection with the new field values:\r\n\r\n![projection_halo_new.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/jzpo5A/images/2071390947-projection_halo_new.png)",
